		"comment": {
			"comments": [
				{
					"id": "289062",
					"author": {
						"name": "tlukasavage",
						"key": "tlukasavage",
						"displayName": "Tony Lukasavage",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"body": "I can get behind this. It is particularly useful with {{build}} since it has a mountain of options. That said, you can always run with {{--no-prompt}} and it will fail and give you the necessary flags/options.",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "tlukasavage",
						"key": "tlukasavage",
						"displayName": "Tony Lukasavage",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"created": "2014-01-21T18:31:38.000+0000",
					"updated": "2014-01-21T18:31:38.000+0000"
				},
				{
					"id": "289069",
					"author": {
						"name": "cbarber",
						"key": "cbarber",
						"displayName": "Chris Barber",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Chicago"
					},
					"body": "Hmm, I don't hate it. :)\n\nWould it be better if after prompting is complete, then displaying a \"Running titanium build -p <platform> ...\" instead? Then someone can just copy and paste the entire command. Or maybe I could inject the final command into the bash history?",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "cbarber",
						"key": "cbarber",
						"displayName": "Chris Barber",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Chicago"
					},
					"created": "2014-01-21T18:42:23.000+0000",
					"updated": "2014-01-21T18:42:23.000+0000"
				},
				{
					"id": "289082",
					"author": {
						"name": "mattapperson",
						"key": "mattapperson",
						"displayName": "me@gmail.com",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"body": "I think doing as the ticket states is great but also inserting the final command into bash history would be amazing",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "mattapperson",
						"key": "mattapperson",
						"displayName": "me@gmail.com",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
					},
					"created": "2014-01-21T19:11:23.000+0000",
					"updated": "2014-01-21T19:11:23.000+0000"
				},
				{
					"id": "289095",
					"author": {
						"name": "fokkezb",
						"key": "fokke",
						"displayName": "Fokke Zandbergen",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "Europe/Amsterdam"
					},
					"body": "Having the full command displayed is nice as well, but not always practical if it is inmediately executed, rapidly pushing the displayed command up away in the console. I would like to have both ;)\n\nUsing {{--no-prompt}} might be to harsh on people, having to retry for every command :S",
					"updateAuthor": {
						"name": "fokkezb",
						"key": "fokke",
						"displayName": "Fokke Zandbergen",
						"active": true,
						"timeZone": "Europe/Amsterdam"
